```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "job_name": "py-slepc4py@3.16.0",
    "account": "use300",
    "reservation": "root_73",
    "partition": "ind-gpu-shared",
    "nodes": 1,
    "tasks_per_node": 1,
    "cpus_per_task": 10,
    "memory": "93G",
    "gpus": 1,
    "time": "00:30:00",
    "output": "%x.o%j.%N",
    "system_name": "expanse",
    "spack_version": "0.17.3",
    "spack_instance_name": "gpu",
    "spack_instance_version": "b",
    "spack_instance_dir": "/cm/shared/apps/spack/0.17.3/gpu/b",
    "scheduler_module": "slurm",
    "spack_package": "py-slepc4py@3.16.0",
    "spack_compiler": "gcc@10.2.0",
    "spack_variants": "",
    "spack_dependencies": "^py-petsc4py@3.16.1/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' py-petsc4py@3.16.1 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} +mpi ^openmpi@4.1.3) ^slepc@3.16.0/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' slepc@3.16.0 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ^petsc@3.16.1 ~complex +mpi ^openmpi@4.1.3)",
    "spack_spec": "py-slepc4py@3.16.0 % gcc@10.2.0  ^py-petsc4py@3.16.1/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' py-petsc4py@3.16.1 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} +mpi ^openmpi@4.1.3) ^slepc@3.16.0/$(spack find --format '{hash:7}' slepc@3.16.0 % ${SPACK_COMPILER} ^petsc@3.16.1 ~complex +mpi ^openmpi@4.1.3)"
  }
}
```
The script is using SLURM as a job scheduler and Spack as a package manager. The script utilizes the following resources:
- **SLURM** for job submission and resource allocation.
- **Spack** for package management, specifically installing the "py-slepc4py@3.16.0" package with its dependencies.
- **gcc@10.2.0** compiler is used to build the packages.
- **openmpi@4.1.3** is used for MPI communication. 
- **petsc@3.16.1** and **slepc@3.16.0** are dependencies of py-slepc4py.
- **py-petsc4py@3.16.1** is another package that depends on petsc and openmpi.
